headline: Trump’s Venezuela oil push unlikely to move needle on prices, analyst warns
summary: Investing.com -- U.S. President Donald Trump’s pledge to unlock more Venezuelan barrels after the capture of President Nicolas Maduro has stirred up geopolitical tensions but is unlikely to dent an already imbalanced, oversupplied oil market, keeping prices under pressure, Kepler Cheuvreux’s Bertrand Hodée warned in a recent note.

headline: US Energy Secretary to discuss Venezuela oil revival with industry execs
summary: Investing.com -- US Energy Secretary Chris Wright plans to meet with oil industry executives this week to discuss revitalizing Venezuela’s energy sector following President Nicolás Maduro’s capture, according to a Bloomberg report Monday.

headline: Is Colgate-Palmolive’s Earnings Beat Streak Reshaping Analyst Expectations And Its Investment Narrative (CL)?
summary: Colgate-Palmolive recently approached its fourth-quarter earnings release, with analysts expecting a single-digit improvement in its bottom line after four consecutive earnings beats. This track record, combined with a consensus “Moderate Buy” rating, highlights how analyst expectations and confidence can shape attention ahead of results. We’ll now examine how Colgate-Palmolive’s consistent earnings outperformance shapes its broader investment narrative amid upcoming quarterly results...

headline: What does the U.S. want from Venezuela after Maduro’s arrest? Wolfe weighs in
summary: Investing.com -- The arrest of Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro has intensified questions about Washington’s strategic goals, but analysts at Wolfe Research argue that the market impact should remain limited.
